# Secrets in this project are stored with Ansible Vault, NOT in a plaintext .env.
#
# The encrypted file secrets/secrets.yml holds MSSQL_PASSWORD and JWT_SECRET_KEY.
# The model service decrypts it at startup using the vault password from
# secrets/.vault_pass (local, git-ignored) or ANSIBLE_VAULT_PASSWORD (CI/CD).
#
# A transient .env is generated ONLY for docker-compose (to configure the MS SQL
# container) by `python scripts/load_secrets.py`, and is deleted right after the
# stack run. You normally never create .env by hand.
#
# Non-secret configuration is set directly on the api service in docker-compose:
#   MSSQL_SERVER=mssql       # compose service name (use localhost only outside Docker)
#   MSSQL_PORT=1433
#   MSSQL_DATABASE=BostonHousingDB
#   MSSQL_USER=sa
#   MSSQL_DRIVER=ODBC Driver 18 for SQL Server
#   JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
#   JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=60

# Kafka (ЛР4):
# - non-secret config (bootstrap_servers / topic / partitions) lives in config.ini [kafka]
#   and is passed to containers via docker-compose environment.
# - the Kafka cluster ID is a secret: add KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID to the encrypted
#   secrets/secrets.yml (Ansible Vault). scripts/load_secrets.py writes it into the
#   transient .env so docker-compose can configure the broker.
